                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="64775" author="youngm" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2011 08:33:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One specific usecase where improving type lookup performance would be beneficial is in the case of an Autowired Provider of a non singleton bean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Autowired Provider&amp;lt;SomeNonSingleton&amp;gt; someBean;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If I&apos;m doing someBean.get() inside of a filter, for example, that makes every request lock on the singleton mutex.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe this issue may be related: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7949&quot; title=&quot;Improve performance of DefaultSingletonBeanRegistry.getSingletonNames(..) for high-concurrent-load applications&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-7949&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-7949&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mike&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65482" author="youngm" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2011 19:48:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue appears to be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6870&quot; title=&quot;Cache by-type lookups in DefaultListableBeanFactory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-6870&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-6870&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79350" author="cbeams" created="Sun, 27 May 2012 09:06:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue duplicates &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-6870&quot; title=&quot;Cache by-type lookups in DefaultListableBeanFactory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-6870&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-6870&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is now resolved.  Please give it a try (available now in 3.2.0.BUILD-SNAPSHOT).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
